msg: Add user customization of environment variables for Windows

author: patrickl
msg: Incorporate Jon Stevens point that we should not distribute a setenv.sh as this will cause overwriting of the user's modified setenv.sh upon upgrade. Now, setenv.sh must be created by the user and if it does not exist (the default), setenv.sh is not sourced.

author: patrickl
msg: Added file for user customizable environment variables such as JAVA_HOME to be saved
